-- Construction Bank Chairman Guo Says Halt of Loans for Developers Unlikely
-- B y   P h i l i p   L a g e r k r a n s e r
-- 2010-11-16T02:14:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-16/construction-bank-chairman-guo-says-halt-of-loans-for-developers-unlikely.html
China Construction Bank Corp. is
unlikely to have stopped loans to property developers, Chairman
Guo Shuqing said today in Beijing.  Guo was responding to a report by the state-run China Real
Estate Business that China’s four largest lenders won’t issue
any new loans to developers for the rest of the year.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
